entries.femaleVariant: Now, as that ol' Greek dawg says, life's a banquet – so don't go thirsty, but don't get drunk, either.
My cue to delta, too. Gotta prep to jack in, be there when you come on comms.
So, not to count chickens, but when'll we see our eddies?
All depends how Ms. Parker avails herself of her role, but a week, two tops is my guess.
And whadda we do while waitin'? Sit around, suck air?
You sit tight, heads down, 'cause ol' uncle Arasaka be watchin'.
DeShawn don't ever work with anyone but the best. I consider Delamain just that.
Yeah, who needs creepy, nosy cab drivers when you've got a clean AI to get you from point A to point B in style?
Hello, Ramón Victorino.
And you're Hannah Conwell.
Ramón – yeah, OK. What do we say we're there for?
Got no questions, all clear.
Got no more questions.
Delamain's our ride there and back?
What kind of cover you get us?
All clear to me.
OK, feel brought up to speed.
Penthouse – how do we get in?
Perfect.
It's fine, Jackie. Don't push it.
Hey, hold on, holmes – who got the Flathead? Who pulled the intel from the braindance?
Jack, it's fine. Don't push it.
Eddies aren't ever most important.
Last thing, Konpeki's got a strict no-iron policy. Security gates, the works.
Fine. Made your point.
Eddies aren't ever most important, Jack.
Fine, Dex. Made your point.
Transport's a Delamain?
These new identities – tell us more. What's our cover?
Biz as usual. Corpo arms deal. Case anyone asks, you there for a bogus meetin' with Arasaka's defense rep – Hajime Taki.
If everythin' goes as planned, Delamain'll drop you back here.
Which is...
The No-Tell Motel. Quiet, no questions asked. Make our next move from there. But I'm flat certain that won't be necessary.
How do we get in the penthouse?
Me and Dex've already covered the fine detes. Ops wise, should be a stroll on the beach.
Elaborate, I wanna hear it.
A Delamain'll drop your asses at the front door of Konpeki Plaza. You'll stroll right in thanks to your false identities.
Anything else?
Goes without sayin' we do this on the hush – ideally no bodies, not a one.
You'll have T-Bug on comms for the duration.
Time for your burnin' questions.
This is where the Flathead comes in.
You'll have to get him in the ventilation shafts, guide him to the dweller and force the dweller to... take a break.
I got a question. When do we get to the real reason we're all here?
Jackie's right. We want more.
You for real?
Drop it, I said. Cut's fair, trust me.
And we're goin' in a hotel full of 'Saka men to swipe some fuckin' toy from the boss' son. We ARE the job.
Hm, and who's providin' transport, a top-tier netrunner and a lead-proof plan and intel?
Sure you wanna go down this road?
Jack's right, Dex. We oughta get more than thirty, we deserve more.
The challenge.
Wanna be remembered for something.
Payback, maybe?
It's about the challenge, always.
Want what everyone worth a damn wants – to be remembered.
Thinkin' Arasaka's due a little payback, overdue…
Hm, respect. Cut you thirty-five for that alone.
Yeah, right. Are you outta your fuckin' mind, V?
Interestin'. So what does qualify as most important?
Wise choice.
Fine. Thirty-five and that's my final offer.
I can live with that… it's my final offer, too.
Hm, been a while since I got a run for my eddies. Actually kinda fun.
Look at you young 'uns makin' us ol' folk look bad.
You wanna build cred, your rep. With you a hundred on that.
Old wounds have yet to heal, huh...?
So you dawgs'll leave your lead-spitters in the ride, take the Flathead inside in its case.
Got some deft suits, so you'll look the part, too.
Tha'ss right, "Excelsior..."
Cold, hard eddies as per usual. Gotta bounce.
Whole family in one place! Hah! Finally!
Well, if it ain't Miss V.
entries.maleVariant: Well, if it ain't Mr. V.

entries.femaleVariant: [Sit]
This.
[Take shard] Let's have a look.
Any thoughts on the plan?
You and Dex – what's your story?
Plan – what's your take?
Enough, I hope, to put me in a luxury Cretan villa from which I'll never set foot in cyberspace again.
No offense, but I'm gonna burn any and all bridges – need a clean break.
You an' Dex known each other a while?
Umm... why?
Ah, y'know, peeps say all kinds of things…
"Everything we hear is an opinion not a fact" – Marcus Aurelius, I think.
Let's get to work!
Go on now, don't be shy!
<kiroshi l="mex" o="¡Chido!" t="Sweet!" b="" a=""/>
C'mon, Dex, isn't that a little low?
Isn't that a little low?
Let's see this bad boy...
Yorinobu's got barely any muscle. Hardest part'll be penthouse security.
Hold on, how you want us to get inside a room you can't get into?
Any other issues, now's your chance.
No more questions. Clear on it all.
I'm good, no questions.
Thanks, T.
Welp, here goes nothin'.
Thanks for your help back at the scav haunt.
A few reapers less in the city – good thing.
Promise to send me a postcard?
Thanks for your help with the scavs, Bug.
[Stand] Let's go.
So, you ready to get goin' or what?
[Stand] Something I gotta take care of first.
Let's roll. No point in waitin'.
In gettin' rich, you mean!
Somethin' I gotta take care of first.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Sin problemas." b="" a=" Meet you by the Delamain."/>
I'd rather not strain my neck when I talk.
Thanks for helping with the scavs, Bug.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Nada mal" b="Preemest cab company in all Night City... " a="…"/>
If things get sticky, he'll head for the safe house.
Huh, you and Dex – both philosophizin'… No wonder you get along.
A'ight, then…
Just don't forget to suit up.
Another offer?
Uh-huh. Kind where we ditch the middleman and split the pot an even fifty-fifty.
entries.maleVariant: Mhm. Kind where we ditch the middleman and split the pot an even fifty-fifty.

entries.femaleVariant: Well as I could've, I guess. Walked around Konpeki Plaza, inside, from that raw BD she scrolled.
Mhm, Bug already filled me in.
So, she just wanna see wha'ss good, or was there somethin' else?
Ahem.
That's it. Let's go over the plan.
Yeah. Parker thinks we don't need you.
I do appreciate you sharin' this info, though, Miss V. You see, trust…
entries.maleVariant: I do appreciate you sharin' this info, though, Mr. V. You see, trust…

entries.femaleVariant: …is essential in any partnership that's to be long-lasting and fruitful.
Ditch the middleman...?
Think she just wanted to see what I was about.
Couldn't've gone better. In fact, she liked me so much, she made me another offer.
There was something else. Parker made me another offer.
Something's off about her.
Parker chick... I dunno – sent out mixed signals, so I got mixed feelings.
Hahaha, sheeit, now that's rich...
Ahaha... AHAHAHAHA!
Clients... never learn, do they?
Let's go over the job.
Appreciation still falls short.
Thought you'd be pissed off.
Thought you'd be pissed, that you'd lose it.
Lived in NC too long to blow my top every time some amateur thinks they can take me for a ride.
Parker ain't the first and sure as hell won't be the last.
Appreciation don't convert to eddies, and Evelyn offered us a bunch.
Y'all need not worry, truly. We'll come to that.
One night – sippin' Champaradise with Yorinobu. Next night – chattin' it up with regulars at Lizzie's... Worlds don't match up.
You sayin' we puttin' two and two together and gettin' five? Some part of the equation's missin' then, clearly.
S'why y'all got a fixer. Anyone try to fuck you, they first gotta fuck their way through Dex DeShawn's three-hundred-pound ass.
Anythin' else?
How 'bout we go over the plan? Whatcha got for us, Dex?
So you know the target. Yorinobu Arasaka. The emperor's son and heir apparent.
Mhm. Man with the million-eddy name and no talent to back it up.
Evelyn Parker's "special friend…"?
V's tellin' it like it is, Dex.
Wanted to see what you was about, huh…?
Set your butts down comfy.
There's something... off about Evelyn.
Cut for fresh talent's always the same and non-negotiable – thirty percent.
Bro, thirty?!
Every part in this drama carries its risks. That's the value of yours as determined by me.
Now's a good a time as any. Fresh talent gets thirty percent always, but I'm willin' to make an exception in your case.
I'ma cut you a nice, juicy forty as a bonus for your honesty, V.
Sounds about right.
Thanks, but the eddies aren't all-important.
That's more like it, Dex.
Appreciate it, Dex. Even though the eddies aren't most important to me.
Ka-ching, baby!
Your chariot awaits outside.
What?!
Struck me too…
Struck me too…
Siddown, le'ss be civilized here, eh?
Sit yo ass down, V.
Evelyn Parker – how'd you fare?
Pretty well. Saw Konpeki Plaza from the inside.
Not bad... But she wants to cut you loose.
First time in realspace.
And how he bags a permit to operate every year's still a mystery.
Trust me when I say whatever hitch you think up, T-Bug's solved it already.
Fine, whatever. Fuck it.
Then, with Bug's help, you'll breach the hotel's subnet…
Mine and the Flathead's help.
Last but not least, you slip into Yorinobu's penthouse and klep the Relic.
Sweet booth. It soundproof?
Jackie...
Heh, City Hall should be fuckin' thankin' us!
City Hall should be fuckin' thankin' us!
Now, now, Mr. Welles is right. We gon' be goin' over some sensitive material.
But if it's all right with y'all, I'd like to start with a question for Ms. V…
entries.maleVariant: But if it's all right with y'all, I'd like to start with a question for Mr. V…

entries.femaleVariant: If we wanna disable, we'll need to neutralize Konpeki's dweller – elite 'runner monitoring the hotel's subnet twenty-four seven.
Only catch is there's no way to get in the dweller's den from the outside.
Flathead'll stay there, jacked into the dweller, but thanks to that I'll be able to roll out your red carpet into the penthouse.
People, after hours, place like this, fifty years on, talking about what I pulled off.
[Put Flathead down]
And the Flathead?
